# Frontend Architecture

Spec: `openspec/specs/frontend-architecture/spec.md`

## HTTP client

- Use `apiClient` from `@/lib/api-client` for all REST calls
- Always `credentials: 'include'` (already set in apiClient)
- Do not add axios or alternate HTTP clients
- Handle errors via `ApiError` (`code`, `message`)

## State layering (strict)

| Data | Where |
|------|-------|
| REST data (balances, orders, markets, klines) | TanStack Query v5 — `hooks/queries/` |
| WebSocket ticker, depth, connection status | Zustand — `stores/market-store.ts`, `stores/ws-store.ts` |
| Current trading pair, chart interval | URL — `/trade/[symbol]`, searchParams |
| Form inputs (price, quantity) | Component `useState` |
| Auth session | `useSession` query → `GET /auth/me`; never store JWT in client |

Never put REST-fetched data into Zustand. After mutations, use `queryClient.invalidateQueries`.

## WebSocket

- Use `useWebSocket` from `@/hooks/use-websocket`
- WS events update Zustand; optionally `queryClient.setQueryData` for order/balance sync

## Auth

- Login/register via `apiClient`; cookies set by server
- Do not read, store, or pass JWT in localStorage, sessionStorage, or Zustand
- Protected pages: wrap with `AuthGuard` or check `useSession`

## UI

- Tailwind only; use semantic color tokens for trading UI
- Import formatters from `@exchange/shared` for all price/quantity/percent display
- New query hooks go in `apps/web/src/hooks/queries/`
